  5 CONCLUSIONS
  A chord detection system is presented which makes use of
  voicing constraints to increase accuracy of chord and chord
  sequence identification. Although the system is developed
  for guitar chords specifically, similar analysis could be per-
  formed to apply these techniques to other constrained en-
  sembles such as choirs or string, wind, or brass ensembles,
  where specific chords are more likely to appear in a particu-
  lar voicing given the constraints of the group.
