  4 IMPLEMENTATION
  4.1 Model Training
  We extract melody range and bass range chromagrams for
  all the songs in the Beatles collection as described in Section2.1.
  The four models that we test are as follows:
  no bass, no duplicate states
  no bass, duplicate states
  bass, no duplicate statesbass, duplicate states
  We divide the 175 hand-annotated songs into five sets,
  each spanning the whole 12 albums. For each of the four
  models we performe a five-fold cross-validation procedure
  by using one set in turn as a test set while the remaining
  four are used to train subchord, chord and chord transition
  models as described in sections 2.3 and 3.1.
