  5 RESULTS
  We calculate the accuracy for the set of chord classes. As
  we have six chord classes (or types), rather than two \[11\]
  or three \[10\] we decided to additionally provide results in
  whichmajor,dominant, andsuspendedchords are merged.
  The calculation of accuracy is done by dividing summed du-
  ration of correctly annotated frames by the overall duration
  of the song collection. Similarly, in the case of one partic-
  ular chord type (or song), this has been done by dividing
  the summed duration of correctly annotated frames of that
  chord type (or song) by the duration of all frames pertaining
  to that chord type (or song).
