  5.2 Total and Chord-specific Accuracy
  Our top performance results (50.9 % for full evaluation mode,
  65.9 % for merged evaluation mode) lie between the top
  scoring results of Lee and Slaney \[11\] (74 %) and Burgoyne
  et al. \[4\] (49 %). This is encouraging as we model more
  chord classes than Lee and Slaney \[11\], which decreases
  accuracy for either of the classes, and their figures refer to
  only the first two Beatles albums, which feature mainlyma-
  jorchords. Unfortunately, we cannot compare results on
  individual chords. We believe that such an overview is es-
  sential because some of the chord types appear so rarely that
  disregarding them will increase total accuracy, but delivers
  a less satisfying model from a human user perspective.
  5.3 Fragmentation
