  p(e\|c)
  .
  The information content can be interpreted as the contextual
  unexpectedness or surprisal associated with an event. Given
  an alphabetEof events which have appeared in the prior
  experience of the model, the uncertainty of the model’s ex-
  pectations in a given melodic context can be defined as the
  entropyor average information content of the events inE:
  H(c)=
