  While there are any number of functions that satisfy the
  requirements of a metric, most are unsuitable for
  meaningful melodic comparison. Since our focus is on
  speeding melodic search, a good metric for melodies must
  be quick to calculate and one where d(X,Y) is small when
  a person would say melodies X and Y are similar and
  d(X,Y) is large when a person would call X and Y
  dissimilar. We now describe a simple metric that has
  proven effective for melodic comparison.
  We represent a melody X as a string of note intervals.
