  6 CONCLUSION
  In this paper, we presented a real-time equalizer of harmonic
  and percussive components in music signals without any a
  priori knowledge of score and included instruments. In au-
  ditory evaluation and experiments, we confirmed the good
  performance. Based on our equalizer, applying existing au-
  dio modification technique as conventional equalizing, re-
  verb, pitch-shift, etc., to harmonic/percussive components
  independently will yield more interesting effect. Applying
  it as pre-processing for multi-pitch analysis, chord detec-
  tion, rhythm pattern extraction, is another interesting future
  work.
