  ISMIR 2008 – Session 2a – Music Recommendation and Organization
  5 CONCLUSION
  We have presented a new approach for the generation of
  playlists using start and end songs and showing inherent se-
  quential order. Our approach is based on audio similarity
  and requires very little user interaction. Both objective eval-
  uation based on genre labels of songs and subjective evalua-
  tion based on listening tests showed that the concept works
  well.
  Our playlist generation algorithm can be utilised by users
  of the website of a public radio station to create their own
  digital “mixtapes” online. Since our evaluation showed that,
  on average, at least one song does not fit the overall playlist,
  an editing functionality might be added to the user interface.
