  4 ADAPTING THE GHSOM FOR PLAYLIST
  GENERATION
  Structuring the music collection under consideration is per-
  formed using an unsupervised neural network algorithm that
  automatically organizes a given data set in a hierarchical
  manner. More precisely, we reimplemented in Java a hier-
  archical extension of the Self-Organizing Map, namely the
  Growing Hierarchical Self-Organizing Map(GHSOM), as
  proposed in \[3\]. The GHSOM has been integrated in the
  CoMIRVA framework \[10\].
  The GHSOM extends the widely used Self-Organizing Map
  \[6\] in a way that during training, new map units are auto-
  matically inserted into the existing grid between the map
  unit whose data items show the highest deviation from the
  map unit’s model vector and its most dissimilar neighboring
  unit. This is performed until the mean quantization error of
  all map units is reduced to a certain thresholdτ
  1
  . Hence,
  τ
  1
  controls the final size of the individual SOMs. A second
  thresholdτ
  2
  determines the quantization error a particular
  map unit must exceed in order to reorganize its data items on
  1
  In our case, the clusters are given by the map units of the Self-
