  4.2 Experiment to investigate how the user feels
  In the second experiment, we investigated whether the user
  felt pleased with the music selected by the proposed system.
  Five subjects (university students) ran on a running machine
  at different paces listening to the music selected by the pro-
  posed system and continued to run until music changed five
  times. They also ran at different paces listening to the mu-
  sic selected by a random selection system. In the random
  selection system, music was selected randomly. Music data
  used in the random selection system was the same as in the
  proposed system. In both cases, they answered how suitable
  each music had been for exercises (“suitability”) and how
  pleasant the whole exercise had been (“pleasingness”) on a
  scale of one to five (Table 3, Table 4). Table 5 illustrates a
