  7 implies that BPM is positively correlated with “suitabil-
  ity”. One subject remarked that he had felt comfortable
  while listening to the music selected by the proposed sys-
  tem especially when running at high SPM. It suggests that
  the proposed system is especially effective when the user is
  running at high SPM. This may be partly because at high
  SPM, phase-shifts are less obtrusive than at low SPM. More
  detailed research will be needed for a complete understand-
  ing of this reason.
