  3 CURRENT DATASETS
  The “Linking Open Data on the Semantic Web” project \[3\]
  hosted by the W3C Semantic Web Education and Outreach
  group aims at publishing a wide range of datasets on the
  Semantic Web, and creating links between them. The cur-
  rently available interlinked datasets (regardless of their do-
  main) can be depicted as in fig. 1. In this section, we discuss
  a few of these datasets and their links to other datasets. We
  especially focus on the music-related datasets we published
  within our DBTune service, using the Music Ontology men-
  tioned above. We illustrate their use by examples of queries
  they can answer, or by tools using their data.
