  and the results given by the Vamp plugin are associated to
  the?resultvariable. The predicatesmo:encodesand
  vamp:qm-keydetectorboth correspond to a particular
  process, which is triggered when the predicate is evaluated.
  Moreover, in the representations ofmo:encodesand
  vamp:qm-keydetector, we can access two statements
  specifying that these arefunctionalproperties
  12
  . For one
  subject of these properties, there is only one correspond-
  ing object. Results corresponding to the evaluation of such
  predicates are therefore cached, to prevent repeating similar
