  5 EVALUATION
  We evaluate each metric algorithm by testing a kNN clas-
  sifier’s ability to recognize the correct album, artist or blog
  that describe each song. We do this by organizing all data
  by ID, and then selecting enough IDs so that we have more
  than 70% of all songs in a training set. The remaining data,
  slightly less than 30%, is a test set. The classifier’s task is to
  look at each test point, and see if at least 2 of its 3 neighbors
  have the desired ID.
  Thus we train a Mahalanobis matrix on a large fraction
  of our data, and test the matrix by measuring identification
