  4\. CLUSTER GENERATION
  4.1. Agglomerative Clustering
  After computing inter-recording dissimilarities, the next
  step is to assign the recordings deemed similar to each
  other to the same cluster. This is done by an hierarchical
  clustering method\[7\], which sequentially merges the
  recordings deemed similar to each other. The similarity is
  inferred from the metric described in Section 3.4. The
  algorithm consists of the following procedure:
  Begin
