  It is also important to look at the non-task-specific\
  systems. For example, the IM system which had the\
  lowest score of all systems over both years was based on\
  the same naïvely constructed spectral feature set (i.e.,\
  MFCC’s, zero-crossing rates, spectral flux, spectral\
  centroid, etc.) as the IM-SVM system that ranked amongst\
  the top systems for the Audio Artist Identification, Audio\
  Genre Classification and Audio Classical Composer\
  Identification tasks in MIREX 2007. The weak\
  performance of the non-task-specific systems strongly\
  suggests that to capture the identity aspects of “music\
  similarity,” one should go beyond simple spectral features.\
  Top-performing systems in ACS 2007 used higher-level\
  features (e.g., rhythm, tonality, tonal sequences, etc.) so as\
  to capture the musically important structures.\
