  selection even harder, since an utterance whose pitch\
  strength is close to the threshold may oscillate between\
  the two classes, which for some applications may be even\
  worst than assigning the whole utterance to the wrong\
  class.\
  Our approach for solving the P/U detection problem is\
  the following. At every instant of time n, we determine\
  the optimal assignment of classes (P/U) to samples in the\
  neighborhood of n, using as optimization criterion the\
  maximization of the distance between the centroids of the\
  classes. Then, we label n with the class whose pitch-\
  strength centroid is closer to the pitch strength at time n.\
  To determine the optimal class assignment for each\
  sample nƍ in the neighborhood of n, we first weight the\
  samples using a Hann window of size 2N+1 centered at n:\
