  This paper is organized as follows. Section 2 presents the\
  sinusoidal model for mixtures of harmonic instruments. In\
  Section 3 we justify the CAM and phase change prediction\
  assumptions and propose an algorithm where these assump-\
  tions are used in a least-squares estimation framework for\
  resolving overlapping harmonics. In Section 4 we present\
  a monaural music separation system which incorporates the\
  proposed algorithm. Section 5 shows quantitative evalua-\
  tion results of our separation system and Section 6 provides\
  a final discussion.\
