  5 EVALUATION\
  5.1 Database\
  To evaluate the proposed system, we constructed a database\
  of 20 quartet pieces by J. S. Bach. Since it is difficult to\
  obtain multi-track recordings, we synthesize audio signals\
  from MIDI files using samples of individual notes from the\
  RWC music instrument database \[15\]. For each line se-\
  lected from the MIDI file, we randomly assign one of four\
  instruments: clarinet, flute, violin or trumpet. For each note\
  in the line, a sample with the closest average pitch is se-\
  lected from the database for the chosen instrument. We cre-\
  ate two source mixtures (using the alto and tenor lines from\
  the MIDI file) and three source mixtures (soprano, alto and\
  tenor), and select the first 5-seconds of each piece for eval-\
  uation. All lines are mixed to have equal level, thus lines in\
