  If we use a valid kernel function, the resulting kernel
  matrixKmust be positive semi-definite. Henceforth, kernel
  matrix and kernel function will be referred to as “kernel” with
  the meaning being clear from the context. Many different
  kernels are used in practice and we have experimented with
  several of them. A natural question that arises is which kernel
  to use. Our work and the work of Lanckriet et al. \[\
  7\] suggests
  that settling for a single kernel may not be optimal and that a
  combination of kernels can improve results.
