  3.2 Rotation-blind dynamic programming
  It is trivial to look at a given onset, pick the tempo and ro-
  tation with the highest score, and call that the short-term
  tempo estimate. However, due to the presence of noise, in-
  evitable onset detection errors, and the matched filter’s far-
  from-perfect powers of auditory source separation, simply
  connecting these short-term tempo estimates does not pro-
  duce a usable estimate of the tempo curve. Better results can
  be achieved by explicitly discouraging large tempo changes.
