  We consider three options for the second part:
  •(T0) removing entirely the tensions and the 6th/7th
  note,
  •(T1) removingentirely the tensions but keeping the
  6th/7th note, and
  •(T2) replacing the whole tension notes with a sin-
  gle bit of information as to whether the chord has any
  tension and keeping the 6th/7th note.
  We also consider the possibility of keeping all the tensions
  intact and keeping the 6th/7th note. We will denote this op-
