  3 VANTAGE INDEXING FOR MANHATTAN EMD
  Vantage indexing (introduced by Vleugels and Veltkamp \[7\])
  is an approach to the retrieval of objects from a large database
  which are similar to a given query. The search is restricted
  to items whose pre-calculated distances to a small set of pre-
  chosenvantage objectsare similar to the query’s distances
  to the same vantage objects.
  3.1 Ball shapes
  If one works with thel
  1
  norm, a ball (the set of all points
  whose distance lies within a certain radius around a point of
  interest) has the shape of a cross-polytope. A one-dimensio-
  nal cross-polytope is a line segment, a two-dimensional cross-
  polytope is a square, for three dimentions, an octahedron,
  and so forth.
